description: It's a gruesome business, but it's a living. HEADHUNTERS are superhuman trackers whose job is to hunt down the ogres of the underworld; the inhuman freak cases the cops can't handle. But can the HEADHUNTERS handle the demonic Army of Wrath and their threat of nuclear holocaust? Writer/artist Chris Marrinan offers a twisted take on the crime fighting genre!

Armstrong fights for his life against a bloodthirsty Dr. Slaughter! The Golden Ghost mysteriously vanishes while tracking down other-worldly assassins! And the rest of the team must contend with ruthless Government agents still investigating the Army of Wrath's suicide nukes!

Joe Theseus has seen the future -- and it's not good. Hermes and The Eyeball Kid are set to get together for a grudge match. The stakes: one lives, one dies. Chryson and Eva Destruction are taking bets on the outcome, the earth below is shaking beneath the onslaught, and before it's all over, Time and Fate themselves will be put in jeopardy. And just who is that hiding in the hatbox, anyway?

The battle of the century rages on! It's Hermes and the Eyeball Kid in a bone-crushing bout to decide the fate of their very lives -- one wins and one dies. Can humanity withstand the heavenly rumblings of these two fated foes? Join Eddie Campbell as the blood stains the canvas, when Hermes versus The Eyeball Kid continues.

The symphony of blood counts off its final notes in the closing issue of this brain-rattling series. Hermes and the Eyeball Kid dole out destruction and mayhem in mammoth chunks, while the very fabric of Fate frays and unravels. As Joe Theseus pursues Rosario through the playground of Destiny, tremors of change set the world aquiver. Who will win, who will die, and will anyone ever be the same again? Find out when the dust settles, as all the answers will be revealed by the rascally Eddie Campbell in the mythic tapestry of Hermes versus The Eyeball Kid #3.

Reggie knows Venture's secret.  So what does a down on his luck, needs a story to make his mark in the world of cut throat journalism?  Simple, create the stories.
 
How does one doe that?  Blackmail the newest (or not so new) hero in town.
name: "Heroes aren't born ..."

description: "Good Samaritan" complex. Problem is, Joe wants to avoid the spotlight at all costs. Undaunted, Reggie comes up with a compromise: Joe will create a super-hero identity, and Reggie will document his activities. Now the attention-starved Reggie and the publicity-shy Joe have to work together to make this business venture succeed. This Issue: When a sea monster attacks the Santa Monica Pier, Reggie sees the perfect opportunity for Venture to grab another headline. But the battle yields revelations about Joe's past... and Reggie's future.
name: "The Call to Battle"

description: Venture meets his arch-nemesis.  The only problem?  He has no idea who this person is.  However luck is shinning upon him as he gets help in the form of Celeste Noble.
name: "The First Final Battle"
